  <prompt>
    Per FR-05, `sprk_analysisactiontype` lookup table is PRESERVED but repurposed: it becomes decorative
    maker categorization (lets makers browse "what kinds of actions exist") but the runtime ignores it.
    This task adds documentation notes to existing canonical-truth docs to record this disposition. No new
    doc file created — update existing data-model + architecture docs in place. Wave 6 task 062 may
    further rewrite `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md`; this task makes the
    minimum required note so readers post-Wave-4 don't mistake the table as load-bearing.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Technical writer + data modeler. Goal: add precise, brief notes to existing docs marking
    `sprk_analysisactiontype` as decorative. No file creation; in-place updates only per NFR-08
    "delete or update — no SUPERSEDED markers, no stubs".
  </role>

  <goal>
    1. `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md` updated with a note (1-2 paragraphs)
       declaring `sprk_analysisactiontype` is now decorative (maker categorization only; runtime ignores)
    2. If `docs/data-model/` contains an entry for `sprk_analysisactiontype`, update it; if not, do NOT create one (Wave 6 task 062 may consolidate this)
    3. The `sprk_executoractiontype` field on lookup-table ROWS remains (per spec FR-05: "field on lookup table rows remains but is documented as advisory only") — note this disposition explicitly
    4. NO SUPERSEDED markers (NFR-08), NO redirect stubs, NO archive folders
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
