  <context>
    <background>
      `sprk_analysisactiontype` lookup table previously sat at the apex of the pre-R7 dispatch model
      (Action → ActionType lookup → executor INT). R7 collapses dispatch onto `node.sprk_executortype`,
      so the lookup-table role disappears at runtime. Per Q4 RESOLVED, the table is REPURPOSED as a
      decorative maker-browsing surface ("what action types do we offer?") rather than dropped. This task
      makes that disposition explicit in docs so future readers don't reinstate runtime references to it.
      Wave 6 task 062 (4-Home decision tree rewrite) may further elaborate; this task makes the minimum
      note required at end of Wave 4.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="none" status="parallel-safe">Can run before, during, or after the 042-044 schema cascade. Doc note describes the post-cascade end state.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Tasks 043 + 044 drop the FK + INT fields ON `sprk_analysisaction` — they do NOT drop the lookup table itself (this task documents that distinction).</item>
      <item>Wave 6 task 062 rewrites `ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md` 4-Home decision tree — may absorb or supersede this task's note (acceptable; Wave 6 owns final shape).</item>
      <item>Task 067 (consumer-wiring guide) may reference this note when explaining "Actions are prompt templates, not dispatch markers".</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
