      If a file exists, plan an in-place update. If absent, DO NOT create a new file (Wave 6 task 062 may consolidate).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author the decorative-note text">
      Write 1-2 paragraphs that:
      - State explicitly: `sprk_analysisactiontype` lookup TABLE is preserved (FR-05); it is decorative maker categorization
      - State explicitly: the runtime dispatch path (PlaybookOrchestrationService.ExecuteNodeAsync) does NOT read it
      - State explicitly: the `sprk_executoractiontype` field on lookup-table ROWS remains but is advisory only
      - State explicitly: dispatch identity lives ONLY on `node.sprk_executortype` (Choice column)
      - Cite FR-03, FR-04, FR-05, FR-07 from spec for traceability
      - Do NOT use words "deprecated", "superseded", "legacy" — per NFR-08, use forward-looking framing ("decorative", "advisory", "informational")
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Apply in-place update to ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md">
      Edit the target section with the new note. Preserve surrounding doc structure. Keep concise (1-2 paragraphs).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Apply in-place update to docs/data-model/ entry if exists">
      If a data-model entry was found in step 3, add a similar note. Do NOT create the file if absent.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Post-update grep — confirm no banned vocabulary">
      Run: Grep pattern="(deprecated|superseded|SUPERSEDED)" path="docs/architecture/ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md"
      Required: zero new instances introduced by this task's edits (pre-existing instances elsewhere are NOT this task's scope — Wave 6 task 069 handles them).
